<!-- SECTION 2: OVERVIEW / INTRO + TL;DR -->
<section class="content-section" id="overview-section">
    <div class="content-container">
        <div class="text-content">
            <h2 class="section-title">UK Company Registration from Delhi - Overview</h2>
            <div class="content-text">
                <div class="highlight-box" style="margin-bottom:20px;">
                    <p><strong>&#128204; TL;DR - UK Company Registration Services at a Glance</strong></p>
                    <p>A UK Private Limited Company (Ltd) is incorporated under the Companies Act 2006 through Companies House. Minimum requirements - 1 director (any nationality, age 16+), 1 shareholder, a UK registered office, GBP 1 paid-up share capital and a PSC register. Since 18 November 2025, new directors and PSCs must complete ECCT 2023 identity verification. Online incorporation 1-2 working days. Corporation Tax 19-25%.</p>
                </div>
                <p><div class='table-responsive-wrapper'>
                <table>
                    <thead><tr><th>Quick Reference</th><th>Details</th></tr></thead>
                    <tbody>
                        <tr><td>Governing Laws</td><td>UK - Companies Act 2006; Corporation Tax Act 2009/2010; Economic Crime and Corporate Transparency Act 2023 (ECCT). India - FEMA 1999 + Overseas Investment Rules / Regulations / Directions 2022. India-UK DTAA (1993; 2012 Protocol effective 27 Dec 2013; MLI PPT effective 1 April 2020)</td></tr>
                        <tr><td>Applicable To</td><td>Indian companies (ODI on automatic route up to 400% of net worth) and resident individuals under LRS (USD 250,000 per FY; financial-services entities NOT permitted)</td></tr>
                        <tr><td>Timeline</td><td>Companies House online 1-2 working days (same-day for GBP 156); UK bank 1-2 weeks (Wise / Revolut / Tide / Mettle) or 4-6 weeks (HSBC / Barclays / NatWest); India-side Form ODI Part I + UIN + remittance 2-3 weeks; end-to-end 4-8 weeks</td></tr>
                        <tr><td>Cost (Indicative)</td><td>Hub 05 cross-list. UK govt fees from 1 Feb 2026 - GBP 100 digital / GBP 156 same-day / GBP 124 paper. Annual Confirmation Statement GBP 50 digital. India advisory bands - Structuring Memo INR 24,999 starting, FEMA ODI Execution INR 49,999 starting, DTAA + MLI PPT Memo INR 49,999 starting</td></tr>
                        <tr><td>UK Corporation Tax (FY25-26 + FY26-27)</td><td>Small profits 19% (up to GBP 50,000); Main rate 25% (above GBP 250,000); Marginal Relief band GBP 50,000-GBP 250,000 (fraction 3/200; effective up to 26.5%); close investment-holding companies 25% flat</td></tr>
                        <tr><td>Forms / Portal</td><td>UK - Companies House WebFiling (incorporation + Confirmation Statement); HMRC (CT600 within 12 months; CT payment 9 months + 1 day). India - Form ODI Part I (pre), Part II (within 30 days), APR (by 31 December), Form OFC (disinvestment)</td></tr>
                        <tr><td>Authority</td><td>UK - Companies House (registrar) + HMRC (tax); India - RBI through AD Category-I Bank + CBDT for treaty interpretation</td></tr>
                    </tbody>
                </table>
                </div></p>
                <p>The United Kingdom remains a top-three destination for Indian outbound business expansion - the gateway to the EU and UK markets, a strong financial centre and home to the deepest English-language legal infrastructure for cross-border deals. A UK Private Limited Company (Ltd) under the Companies Act 2006 is the standard vehicle for Indian founders entering the UK or EU market and the incorporation process through Companies House is among the fastest in the world (1-2 working days online). Two recent regulatory shifts matter for any Indian founder forming a UK Ltd in 2026 - the Economic Crime and Corporate Transparency Act 2023 (ECCT) introduced mandatory identity verification for directors and Persons with Significant Control from 18 November 2025 (with enforcement against existing officeholders from 18 November 2026) and Companies House fees rose significantly on 1 February 2026 (digital incorporation doubled from GBP 50 to GBP 100; annual Confirmation Statement rose from GBP 34 to GBP 50).</p>
                <p>Content is reviewed quarterly for accuracy.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<!-- SECTION 3: WHAT IS GSTAT APPEAL FILING -->
<section class="content-section" id="what-section">
    <div class="content-container">
        <div class="two-column">
            <div class="column-content">
                <h2 class="section-title">What Is a UK Private Limited Company?</h2>
                <div class="content-text what-is-definition">
                    
                    <p>A UK Private Limited Company (Ltd) is a separate legal entity incorporated under the <strong>Companies Act 2006</strong> and registered with <strong>Companies House</strong>, the UK's national company registrar. It is the standard vehicle for both UK residents and foreign founders, including Indian residents. A Ltd requires:</p>
<ul>
    <li>At least 1 director (a natural person aged 16 or older; any nationality; <strong>UK residency NOT required</strong>)</li>
    <li>At least 1 shareholder (can be the same person as the director)</li>
    <li>A UK registered office address (a real address that receives statutory mail)</li>
    <li>GBP 1 minimum paid-up share capital</li>
    <li>A Persons with Significant Control (PSC) register declaring those with 25% or more of shares, voting rights or significant influence over the company</li>
</ul>

<p>Since <strong>18 November 2025</strong>, the <strong>Economic Crime and Corporate Transparency Act 2023 (ECCT)</strong> makes identity verification mandatory for new directors and PSCs at the time of appointment. Existing officeholders have a 12-month transition window with enforcement from <strong>18 November 2026</strong>. Identity verification is conducted directly by Companies House or through an <strong>Authorised Corporate Service Provider (ACSP)</strong>, which is the new regulated actor under ECCT.</p>

<p>Company secretaries are NOT mandatory for private Ltd companies under Section 270 Companies Act 2006, which simplifies governance for foreign founders. The UK Companies House fee schedule was revised on <strong>1 February 2026</strong> - digital incorporation rose from GBP 50 to GBP 100, same-day digital from GBP 78 to GBP 156, paper incorporation to GBP 124 and the annual Confirmation Statement (digital) from GBP 34 to GBP 50.</p>

<p>Delhi anchors this engagement because of the highest concentration of British educational and professional links in India, the UK High Commission's presence and the India-UK BCCI office. Patron's engagement covers both legs - UK Ltd incorporation through an Authorised Corporate Service Provider partner in London plus the India-side FEMA Overseas Investment Rules 2022 compliance through an Authorized Dealer Category-I bank in Delhi.</p>

                </div>
                <div class="highlight-box" style="margin-top:20px;">
                    <p><strong>Key Terms for UK Company Registration:</strong></p>
                    <p><strong>UK Private Limited Company (Ltd):</strong> Separate legal entity under Companies Act 2006; limited liability; standard vehicle for SMEs and foreign founders.</p>
<p><strong>Companies House:</strong> UK's national company registrar - an executive agency of the Department for Business and Trade.</p>
<p><strong>ECCT Act 2023:</strong> Economic Crime and Corporate Transparency Act 2023 - mandatory ID verification for company officers and PSCs; enhanced Companies House powers.</p>
<p><strong>ID Verification:</strong> Mandatory identity check via Companies House One Login or ACSP - required from 18 November 2025 for new directors and PSCs.</p>
<p><strong>ACSP:</strong> Authorised Corporate Service Provider - regulated entity (typically accountancy or law firm) that conducts ID verification and files on behalf of clients under ECCT.</p>
<p><strong>PSC Register:</strong> Persons with Significant Control register - disclosure of individuals or entities holding 25%+ shares, voting rights or significant influence.</p>
<p><strong>Marginal Relief:</strong> Corporation tax relief for profits in the GBP 50,000-GBP 250,000 band; fraction 3/200; effective rate up to 26.5% per HMRC CTM03900.</p>
<p><strong>Confirmation Statement:</strong> Annual Companies House filing; GBP 50 digital from 1 Feb 2026.</p>
<p><strong>CT600:</strong> Corporation Tax return to HMRC within 12 months of period end; CT payment 9 months + 1 day after period end.</p>
<p><strong>MLI:</strong> Multilateral Convention - in force for India from 1 Oct 2019; effective for India-UK DTAA from 1 April 2020 with PPT under Article 7.</p>
<p><strong>FEMA OI Rules 2022:</strong> India-side outbound investment framework effective 22 Aug 2022.</p>
<p><strong>India-UK DTAA:</strong> Signed 25 Jan 1993; in force 25 Oct 1993; 2012 Protocol effective 27 Dec 2013.</p>

                </div>
            </div>
